				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Please someone explain to me....<a name="56967"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 16 04 3:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>A raid is any battle where more than one full group is involved.  The distinction &quot;raid only&quot; is an artificial one.  Mobs loot tables are, in general, the same no matter who or how many kill them.  But a lot of mobs just aren't going to be killed by one group.  It takes substantial numbers of folks to kill them so they are considered raid targets and their loot is something you aren't going to see unless you're part of a raid that kills them.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
